HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1193
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Officer Ryan Berg upon
his receipt of the Purple Heart Medal.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Officer Ryan Berg, who was recently honored with the
Chattanooga Police Department's Purple Heart Medal, in recognition of his exceptional bravery,
resolve, and commitment to duty in the face of extreme peril; and
WHEREAS, on December 28, 2025, Chattanooga Police Officers responded to a report
of shots fired on Highway 53; Officer Ryan Berg, along with assisting officers, located the
suspect upon arrival and attempted to make contact; and
WHEREAS, the suspect immediately opened fire, striking Officer Berg, who sustained
significant injuries to his hand and face; Officer Berg was transported to Erlanger Emergency
Room by Hamilton County EMS and required multiple surgeries, and the suspect was ultimately
taken into custody; and
WHEREAS, Officer Ryan Berg's bravery in the face of danger truly demonstrated his
dedication to protecting and serving his community and his commitment to the welfare and
safety of others; and
WHEREAS, the selfless service and resilience provided by Officer Ryan Berg have
made a lasting impact on the Chattanooga Police Department, and he is an inspiration to all;
now, therefore,
HJR1193
016040
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Officer Ryan Berg upon his receipt of the Purple
Heart Medal from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
